    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>A hail of rock-hard ice pounds to the ground in a 20-foot-radius, 40-foot-high cylinder centered on a point within range. Each creature in the cylinder must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/damage 2d8 type=bludgeoning]] damage and [[/damage 4d6 type=cold]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>Hailstones turn the storm's area of effect into &amp;Reference[rule=difficultterrain]{difficult terrain} until the end of your next turn.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p></p><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"At Higher Levels\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"1\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the bludgeoning damage increases by [[/damage 1d8]] for each slot level above 4th.</p></div></div>",
